The three tracts contained in Cod. A. were not originally bound together into one volume. This may be seen, not so much from the separate paging of each tract, as from the circumstance that they have not been bound in the same order in which they were written. The first in date was the “De veritate sa'crae scripturae'': then came the “De dominio divino”‚ and lastly “De ecclesiaf': in the present volume how- ever “De ecclesia'' is placed in the middle.
